-- Monte dei Paschi shares plunge more than 16 percent
-- By Danilo Masoni
-- Thu Oct 30, 2014 08:57AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, Oct 30 (Reuters) - Shares in Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena <BMPS.MI>, which faces a 2.1 billion euro capital shortfall after EU-wide stress tests of lenders, continued to fall to fresh record lows on Thursday and was suspended after a drop of more than 16 percent.

